# 3. ドタバタの再会

Miku: <...and Kohane ended up singing with those girls?>
An: Yeah! It was super awesome. The crowd went totally wild.
Miku: <I see. I would've liked to see that.>
Toya: They said that they sing there from time to time, so we may encounter them again if we're lucky.
Kohane: We'll make sure to let you know when that happens, Miku. They really are amazing singers.
Miku: <Hehe. I'm looking forward to it already.>
Akito: Oh, I think I see it.
Akito: That must be the venue for the flea market.
Kohane: Wow, this is amazing... Look at all the shops...!
Akito: Secondhand clothing, tableware, antique objects, paintings... They've really got it all.
Toya: It's quite the selection. Where should we begin?
An: Hmm... I wanna check out that shop's trinkets and stuff, but I'm also interested in the clothes over there!
An: Oh, but I also see some really nice accessories over there... I-I can't decide...!
Toya: It seems we may be here quite a while.
Akito: Yeah... I'm getting kinda hungry, so I'm gonna go buy a hot dog. Make up your mind before I get back, okay?
An: Okay.
Miku: <Oh, a real hot dog stand? I'd like to see what that's like.>
Akito: Then, let's go together. You want one, Toya?
Toya: Yes, please.
Akito: Alright, I'll get two.
Akito: Umm... “Two hot dogs, please.”
Vendor: “$4.95 for one, and $9.90 for two!”
Akito: $9.90, got it. Where's my wallet...
Miku: (Huh?)
Miku: (That boy's sprinting straight this way for some reason.)
Miku: <...! Akito, look out!>
Akito: Huh?
Akito: Whoa...!
Toya: Is everything okay, Akito?!
Akito: Yeah... Sorry, Miku. I dropped my phone...
Miku: <Forget about me! Right now...>
Miku: <You need to get your wallet back!>
Akito: What?
Miku: <That boy just ran off with your wallet!>
Akito: Huh...?
An: What?! Your wallet got stolen?!
Akito: Seriously?! Which way did he go?!
Toya: Akito, wait! He may be carrying a weapon. It's too dangerous to chase after him without a plan!
Boy: “Tourists are so easy! And there's plenty of people here, so I should be able to get away...”
???: “Hey, we saw that!”
???: “That wallet doesn't belong to you, now does it?”
Kohane: What's going on over there?
An: Did someone catch him for us?! We gotta go see!
Akito: Wait, they're...!
An: The twins we met that time...?!
Slade: “If you know what's good for you, then you'll stop picking people's pockets!”
Boy: “Sh-Shut up!”
Kohane: Oh, there he goes...
Toya: I'm glad they were able to get your wallet back safely. But...
Slade: Long time no see, you guys! Here's your wallet, Akito!
Akito: Th-Thanks... I appreciate it.
Akito: More importantly, what are you guys doing here?!
Slade: We came to do some shopping. This area's more or less where we're based.
Cedric: We just happened to spot you guys.
Cedric: But just as we were coming to talk to you, that kid came by and took your wallet. So, we decided to catch him.
An: I see...
Akito: Again, I really appreciate it... But to think that we'd meet again like this.
Slade: Haha. I know, right?! But it really is nice to see you guys again.
Slade: Just a guess, but... Does this mean you guys are here to see SONIC NOTES?
An: Huh? How did you know?
Cedric: Taiga's performing, after all. Also, there was no way you'd miss such a big event.
Cedric: Not if you're aiming to be world-class.
Akito: You guys said that when we met you in Japan. You're serious about standing on top of the world too, huh.
An: Also, you two said that you knew Aunt Nagi.
An: How is it that you guys knew her?
Slade: Oh, right... We were in such a rush that we didn't get a chance to explain.
Slade: I know! We should go to a cafe or something and have us a nice, long chat! How does that sound?
Cedric: Wait, don't just assume that they're free. You can see they're in the middle of sightseeing.
An: We're totally fine to join you guys! We don't have any plans until SONIC NOTES starts, so I'd sure love to ask you two some questions.
Slade: Then, we can talk at this one cafe we go to all the time. The coffee there's really amazing!
Toya: Amazing coffee? That sounds very nice.
Cedric: Then, we'll lead the way. Follow us, you guys.
Kohane: Okay, we're right behind you!
